2 pictures, years apart. .
My story began in Tangerang, been practicing piano for 13 years now, I've gone through ups and downs more than anyone can imagine, the pain and bitter of failing, the sweetness of winning in front of hundreds. .
And every single day in this 13 years time made me the pianist I am today. If you can overcome those days when your excuses and fears and hatred of putting in the discipline and hard work are so intense, then I can assure you, you can make it! this applies to anyone pursuing anything! For me, I had around 3 major years in where I'd love to throw in the towel. I did once, but thank Jesus I was given a second chance through the best teacher I've ever met. BUT not everyone would get second chance right?
.
All this time you see all of the goods in being able to play musical instruments, but you never knew how much hard works, time, and most of all sacrifices (no partying, no hanging out, no this, no that) have to be made. And for that, you'll have to be ready to be mocked, misunderstood, shunned, and people would think you're mad. All those quotes and motivations you read these days, they're all true, and yet everything's much easier said than done.
.
So I hope now you understand that the glamours, glitters, golds you see in people, it's all built through perseverance, sacrifices more than you ever thought (and maybe you'd ever make). And yes talent does make difference, BUT you're plain ignorant if you're having this talent thing as your excuse. .
All in all, Jesus guided me throughout all these things and that's the most important thing, and for me, supports from families, especially parents, make up 50% of one's robust mentality when facing difficult time. That being said, I hope that yall, as parents (or when you become one), support your kids in whatever they love!
.
Acknowledge that everything's from God and thus give all the glories and honors to God and God only. ‚úù
.
